Okwe Obi, Abuja President Muhammadu Buhari is expected to sign the 2018 Appropriation Bill of N9.12 trillion into law today. Minister of information and Culture, Alhaji Lai Muhammed, had earlier confirmed that the signing ceremony had been scheduled for yesterday (Tuesday). Buhari had, on May 25, received the 2018 budget, six months after it was presented to the National Assembly. On May 16, 2018, Â the National Assembly passed the N9,120,334,988,225, with about N500 billion increase.
Signing of the budget is expected to take place at Aso Rock, Abuja.